# NavLink Component Rules

## Overview
Rules and patterns for the NavLink component (`src/components/atoms/NavLink.tsx`)

## Purpose
Individual navigation link with consistent styling and hover states

## Rules

### Core Requirements
- ✅ **Required Props:** Both `href` and `label` are required (no defaults)
- ✅ **TypeScript:** Use explicit prop types with required string properties
- ✅ **Styling:** Consistent hover states with brand color transition
- ✅ **Typography:** Fixed font size (`text-[16px]`) for consistency
- ✅ **Accessibility:** Use semantic Link component from Next.js
- ✅ **State Management:** Hover state transitions to brand color (`hover:text-[#8a0028]`)
- ✅ **Color Scheme:** Default gray (`text-gray-800`) with brand color on hover

## Code Template
```typescript
import Link from "next/link";

type NavLinkProps = {
  href: string;
  label: string;
};

export function NavLink({ href, label }: NavLinkProps) {
  return (
    <Link
      href={href}
      className="text-gray-800 hover:text-[#8a0028] transition-colors text-[16px]"
    >
      {label}
    </Link>
  );
}

export default NavLink;
```

## Implementation Details

### Props
- `href` (required): Navigation destination
- `label` (required): Display text for the link
- Type: Both are `string`

### Styling Classes
- Base: `text-gray-800`
- Hover: `hover:text-[#8a0028]`
- Transition: `transition-colors`
- Typography: `text-[16px]`

### Color Scheme
- Default text: Gray 800 (`text-gray-800`)
- Hover text: Brand color (`text-[#8a0028]`)
- Transition: Smooth color transition

## Usage Examples

### Basic Usage
```typescript
<NavLink href="/menu" label="Menu" />
<NavLink href="/about" label="About" />
```

### In Navigation Components
```typescript
{NAV_ITEMS.map((item) => (
  <NavLink key={item.label} href={item.href} label={item.label} />
))}
```

